<title>UK: Northern Leisure surges on year results.</title>
<headline>Northern Leisure surges on year results.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Northern Leisure surged to a record peak after the entertainment group reported that its full-year pre-tax profits jumped by 46 percent, traders said.</p>
<p>AT 0838 GMT, the shares were up 20p to 158p, after stretching to a new high at 160p.  </p>
<p>In addition, the company, whose full year profits rose to 5.51 million stg in the year from 3.77 million stg in the previous year, said it saw profits for 1997 being &quot;materially greater&quot; than 1996 because of improved trading conditions.</p>
<p>--Debra Sherman, London newsroom +44 171 542 4026</p>
